lenders.name: Rebecca
lenders.loan_because:
In 1985 I was an exchange student to Kenya, living in Mombasa and attending school there.  Although that was many years ago, I still feel an affinity for my host country, so predominantly make loans to Kenyans.

We have very recently moved to a small property where we keep four chickens and are raising a calf.  My husband has started making our vegetable garden and we have plans for some other small-scale self-sufficiency.  

Generally we make loans based on some there being some affinity with our experiences/interests - so made loans to borrowers with agricultural aspirations, long before we had the opportunity to rent a farm of our own!

lenders.name: LLL Team Fund
lenders.loan_because:
This fund is managed by members of the Late Loaning Lenders Team for the purpose of supporting loans that are on the verge of expiring. We lend to help avoid expiry without regard to gender, region, sector or loan terms. This is in keeping with the team philosophy of every loan deserving to be raised.

We welcome donations in the form of Kiva Gift Certificates which you can send by email to kiva.lll.fund@gmail.com. These donations are not tax-deductible.
Money in the fund cannot be withdrawn.
